properties.name: London
properties.narrative: It's big and intimate. It's noisy and calm. It's in your face, and aloof. It's frantic claustrophobia and then the loneliest place in the world. You can't ignore it. You can't die without seeing it.
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of England and the largest and most cosmopolitan city in Europe.

properties.name: Carlisle
properties.narrative: The city traces its origins to a 1st-century Roman outpost associated with Hadrian's Wall. Carlisle Cathedral, founded in the 12th century, i
properties.shortnarra: The largest city in England by area.

properties.name: Coventry
properties.narrative: Coventry is a large ? originally medieval - city which sustained quite considerable destruction at the hands of the Luftwaffe in November 1940. Architectural gems remain, and these days it?s a lively place and one worth exploring ? particularly the Guild
properties.shortnarra: Coventry is both an industrial centre and a cathedral city, combining industry with culture in an interesting combination. Locally, the city is known as the Three Spired Jewel.

properties.name: Copenhagen
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of Denmark.

properties.name: Stockholm
properties.shortnarra: Watery and beautiful ancient capital of Sweden, scattered across a number of islands, each with their own character.

properties.name: SCOTLAND
properties.shortnarra: Scotland is mysterious and beautiful. From deep, icy cold lochs and monsters, to up to the minute, cutting-edge bars and clubs, Scotland has it all. Beautiful, remote and cool.

properties.name: WALES
properties.shortnarra: Often described as 'rainy but picturesque', this proud and individual country offers green mountains, sandy beaches and soft lilting accents. And rugby, just about everywhere you go.

properties.name: LITHUANIA
properties.shortnarra: Lithuania is mostly flat and quite extensively forested. In those forests lie cool cities, heritage sites and castles. It has a coastal area on the Baltic, to which you can run to catch some rays.

properties.name: LATVIA
properties.shortnarra: From the capital Riga's pretty medieval streets and statue of lady liberty to the serene beauty and fresh air of Gauja National Park, you'll find something to love here. Don't forget to have a sauna ..

properties.name: FINLAND
properties.shortnarra: Finland is wild. Outside of the metropolis of Helsinki, this place is wild. It's also a country of contrasts. Love nature and the outdoors? Finland, like its Scandinavian cousins, does this sooooo well

properties.name: NORWAY
properties.narrative: Conduct any outdoor activity you fancy - whether it be whilst gazing at the northern lights, getting confused under the midnight sun or getting nervous while approaching an elk on a wildlife safari. You can fish, hike or - if there's snow on the ground -
properties.shortnarra: One of the most beautiful countries in the world, Norway is a real jaw-dropper. Forget vikings - think rocky coastlines, wild mountains (and trolls), deep fjords and villages of white, timber houses.

properties.name: Lyon
properties.narrative: Lyon was founded on the Fourvi�re hill as a Roman colony in 43 BC. It subsequently became the capital of Gaul. Today, the archbishop of Lyon is still referred to as "Primat des Gaules" and the city often referred to as th
properties.shortnarra: Roman ruins, Cathedrals and Churches, Medieval streets and parks and gardens make Lyon a pleasant place to hole up for a day or two.

properties.name: SWEDEN
properties.narrative:
Large towns and cities are the place to bolt to for some serious fish-food and drinking. Swedes have got style and a dignified manner down to fine arts; Ikea is but a simplification of a complex national psyche - but it gives a basic idea.

An app
properties.shortnarra: An enormous land of lakes, forests and - at least at its northern Lapland region - brooding mountains and seemingly endless 'sky'. Another great advocate of the outdoors - Sweden is just so ... healthy

properties.name: Chester
properties.narrative:
This is the only city which is completely encircled by surviving roman walls - not even York's walls are this intact.

Architecturally, Chester is incredibly diverse and important. There are buildings from different periods of history and of cours
properties.shortnarra: A combination of Roman and medieval relics, and many timber-framed buildings make this an interesting and pretty old city.

properties.name: Cannes
properties.narrative: Its moment to shine arrives in May as the venue for the Cannes Film Festival, entertaining the rich and famous. During the festival, fans can see actors, celebrities, and directors up close and in person on the famous steps of the Palais des Festivals at
properties.shortnarra: Once a small fishing village, Cannes is now a glamorous and expensive seaside town considered to be one of the social hubs of Europe.

properties.shortnarra: A continent of contrasts. Great wealth and poverty. Khoisan clicks, great stillness. Monochromatic barren landscapes yet deep, lush greenery. Amazing wildlife. The memory of Africa will stay forever.

properties.name: ASIA
properties.narrative:
Regions:


Countries:


Cities:


Other destinations:


History:

<
properties.shortnarra: The world's largest and most diverse continent, has it all. Shiny-new buildings next to the crumbling ancient ones, soft sandy beaches and the throbbing metropolis. Heavy, oppressive jungles. ALL!

properties.name: AUSTRALIA/OCEANIA
properties.narrative:
Regions:


Countries:


Cities:


Other destinations:


History:

<
properties.shortnarra: Defined by the new and the old, this area has long been the plundering grounds for film-location research. It's easy to see why. Soft, white beaches, ancient tradition and great beauty at every turn.

properties.name: Kingston Upon Hull
properties.narrative:
Hull was completely battered during World War II. It was one of the hardest hit cities in the north of England. A lot of the buildings are therefore rather modern. Hull makes up for this with LOTS of flower beds. It's very proud of them.

Hull off
properties.shortnarra: The city which cradled the man who abolished the slave trade throughout the Empire.

properties.name: Oxford
properties.narrative: <!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:View>Normal</w:View> <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom> <w:Compatibility> <w:BreakWrappedTables/> <w:SnapToGridInCell/> <w:WrapTextWithPunct/> <w:UseAsianBreakRules/> </w:Compatibility> <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplor
properties.shortnarra: The great university town, with academia, achievement and history bleeding from almost every building. The university is the second oldest in Europe, after the Sorbonne in Paris.

properties.name: SWITZERLAND
properties.shortnarra: The land of towering mountains and meadows, glittering high waterfalls and an impossibly clean and efficient country. Switzerland is also known for the legend of its national hero - William Tell.

properties.name: BULGARIA
properties.shortnarra: An unexplored, and unspoiled, country with many amazing man-made and natural sights; forts, ruins, amazing cities and natural caverns, arches and caves. If you fancy the beach, it has those too ...

properties.name: ICELAND
properties.narrative: <font color="#000000">There are several familiar associations: hip Reykjav�k, the beautiful therapeutic Blue Lagoon, or perhaps our musical exports Bj�rk or Sigur R�s. But this land of boiling mud pools, spurting geysers, glaciers and waterfalls is also
properties.shortnarra: Hilariously, this place is really quite green. 'Greenland' is actually rather 'icy'. Furious fiery activity, crashing clear water and steel-blue ice come together in nature's most dramatic show.

properties.name: Kristianstad
properties.shortnarra: Former garrison town, this city - founded by Danish Kristian IV - making good of itself and the beautiful surrounding area.

properties.name: St Albans
properties.shortnarra: Truly beautiful historic city, with its foundations being laid in prehistory. There are many medieval buildings remaining and this place truly is ancient.

properties.name: Genoa
properties.narrative:
An ancient city with a new coat on. You have to do a bit of walking to find the real treats in this busy city but they're there for the grabbing.

The historic centre of Genoa is the largest in Europe and many tiny alleys twist and turn away from
properties.shortnarra: Sixth largest city in Italy and birthplace of the explorer Christopher Columbus.

properties.name: Plymouth
properties.narrative: The Pilgrim Fathers left for the New World (America) in 1620 near to where the "Mayflower Steps" can be found.
properties.shortnarra: In the Barbican area of this historic maritime city there are around 100 listed buildings and reportedly the largest concentration of cobbled streets in Britain.

properties.name: BELGIUM
properties.shortnarra: More than just Poirot and TinTin, Belgium is an overlooked, culturally and naturally blessed, gem. Many people are discovering what this misunderstood country has to offer.

properties.name: Moscow
properties.shortnarra: Capital City of the Central Federal District of European Russia

properties.name: Pokhara
properties.shortnarra: Pokhara is the third largest city in Nepal. It is the starting point for most of the treks in the Annapurna area. It is considered by many to be the most beautiful place in the whole wide world.

properties.name: Durham
properties.narrative:
Durham is well known for its Norman cathedral and 11th-century castle, both UNESCO World Heritage Sites. The castle has been the home of Durham University since 1832.

The River Wear sweeps through and around the city, and Du
properties.shortnarra: A forgotten outpost, this northern gem is well worth the long trip from London to see it.

properties.name: EUROPE
properties.narrative:
Regions:


Countries:


Cities:


Other destinations:


History:

<
properties.shortnarra: Self-styled 'Cradle of Western Civilization', Europe is without question a deep-thinking and stylish travel heavyweight - impressive history, culture and sheer diversity.

properties.name: Paris
properties.shortnarra: Paris! Ahhh! Oui, oui; La Ville De L'amour, La Ville des lumi�res. And of course "La Ville De crotte de chien" - but don't let that disturb you

properties.name: Lincoln
properties.shortnarra: Famed for its splendid cathedral, Lincoln is a pleasant, green and beautiful city.

properties.name: Warwick
properties.narrative: <!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:View>Normal</w:View> <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom> <w:Compatibility> <w:BreakWrappedTables/> <w:SnapToGridInCell/> <w:WrapTextWithPunct/> <w:UseAsianBreakRules/> </w:Compatibility> <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplor
properties.shortnarra: This city is dominated by the heavy presence of the immense, immovable fortress that is Warwick Castle. The Earls of Warwick still live here to this day.

properties.name: Worcester
properties.narrative:
Don't ponder upon its porcelain, glower at its glove-making or sneer at its sauce, Worcester is worth more than these stereotypes.

Check out instead the old timbered houses of Friar Street, Fish Street and the buildings around Upper Tything and o
properties.shortnarra: This old city has a fine cathedral and spans both banks of the River Severn. Just about everyone throughout history has attempted to grab a bit of Worcester. It's that good.

properties.name: SLOVAKIA
properties.shortnarra: A young country, with old traditions and folklore, Slovakia is full of Gothic religious buildings, tangled and stoned medieval towns and the whole dramatic landscape is dotted with caves and castles.

properties.name: Cambridge
properties.shortnarra: A beautiful and ancient place which is known best for its university. Settlement in this area has been traced back as far as 3,500BC and there are many famous sights in this magical place.

properties.name: LUXEMBOURG
properties.shortnarra: It has been wedged in the armpits and crotches of a number of other surrounding countries. This intense pressure has forced the fusion of Germanic and Romance lands.

properties.name: Ghat (Arabic: ???? ??t)
properties.narrative: <font color="#000000">(Arabic: ???? ??t)</font><div><font color="#000000">In historical times, Ghat was a major terminal point on the Trans-Saharan trade route and a major administrative center in the Fezzan. It was a stronghold for the Kel Ajjer Tuareg

properties.name: GREECE
properties.shortnarra: White beaches, unspoilt villages and beautiful people, here is a must-see. All of it. Eat fresh food produced from the hills and turquoise seas whilst reading the mythology behind the NEXT sight ...

properties.name: CROATIA
properties.shortnarra: Croatia harks back to a time when the mediterranean wasn't so ... *spoiled*. Although Dubrovnik jostles busily with yachts, other secret, beautiful spots down this vast coast remain to be discovered.

properties.name: BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA
properties.shortnarra: Bosnia is the northern, Herzegovina the southern, area. You can hike in the north-west, discover rich history in the centre, explore villages in the south west and the mountains in the south east.

properties.name: ROMANIA
properties.narrative: Romania is up and coming. It is beautiful and evolving - Bucharest thumps and flashes at the visitor, while the countryside is largely untouched and simple. Traditional farmers transport their materials by simple horse-drawn cart and children play in the
properties.shortnarra: The country of vampires. It was from the dark and forbidding Transylvania region the sinister creature was supposed to have sprung. Alternatively, people see simplicity, purity and endless outdoor fun.

properties.name: Nuuk
properties.shortnarra: Capital City of Greenland and northernmost capital city in the world. Brrrrr, but beautiful.

properties.name: Andorra la Vella
properties.shortnarra: Capital of Andorra.

properties.name: IRELAND
properties.shortnarra: The accent is charming. So are the people. This Emerald Isle is charming. Green and beautiful and offering a rugged countryside in which to get lost, be careful how you go. You may not want to leave.

properties.name: Belgrade
properties.shortnarra: Capital City of Serbia.

properties.name: AUSTRIA
properties.shortnarra: Beautiful and decadent, Austria blasts you with chocolate-box imagery of dramatically beautiful mountain scenery. The cities also buzz - but not at the expense of 'olde worlde' charm and simplicity.

properties.name: ITALY
properties.shortnarra: Italy has always been a geographical by-word for the good life - 'La Dolce Vita' - and examples of people benefiting from it can be seen in every estate and on every street corner.

properties.name: Zagreb
properties.shortnarra: Capital city of Croatia

properties.name: SPAIN
properties.shortnarra: Barren spaces and great beauty, a glut of coast and beaches and both relaxed and passionate (sometimes the switch happening within seconds), Spain has everything. Hire a car and go exploring ...

properties.name: Warsaw
properties.shortnarra: Capital city of Poland

properties.name: DENMARK
properties.shortnarra: A viking stronghold which was never truly conquered, offering beer, bacon and belting good hospitality. From Copenhagen, to the unspoiled medieval town of Rebe, Denmark has style in spades.

properties.name: Sheffield
properties.narrative: During the 19th century, Sheffield gained an international reputation for steel production. Many innovations were developed locally, including crucible and stainless steel, fuelling an almost tenfold increase in the population during the Industrial Revol
properties.shortnarra: The Rome of the North, the city nestles in a natural amphitheatre created by several hills

properties.name: Budapest
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of Hungary.

properties.name: Norwich
properties.shortnarra: Beautiful old city well known for its long association with Colman's mustard.

properties.name: Peterborough
properties.shortnarra: Ancient city, often misconstrued but which always surprises the uninformed. Peterborough is old, beautiful and rich in history.

properties.name: Leicester
properties.shortnarra: A multi-cultural, diverse mix permeates everything in this friendly, interesting city. Large parts of the city were destroyed in bombing raids during WWII, but there are still some gems to be found.

properties.name: NETHERLANDS
properties.shortnarra: Liberalism, tulips, dykes and storks spring to mind with this friendly place. Amsterdam maintains the cultural speed of Europe whilst smaller cities and towns preserve a modicon of calm and ease.

properties.name: ENGLAND
properties.shortnarra: England is known throughout the world. It is a tiny country which has produced some big, big, concepts and characters. The cradle of the BBC, the language itself, of Shakespeare and many others.

properties.name: GERMANY
properties.shortnarra: Seen as the grown-up sensible one in Europe, Germany has a 'stern' reputation. Postcard perfect castles, dark forests and medieval cities, surround a friendly population keen on welcoming you here.

properties.name: Ljubljana
properties.shortnarra: The beautiful capital city of Slovenia. Apparently founded by Jason (of the Argonauts fame).

properties.name: Salisbury
properties.shortnarra: Beautiful city with timbered buildings, towering Cathedral, bustling local market and many museums and historic houses to explore. An ideal base to explore Wiltshire.

properties.name: Exeter
properties.shortnarra: This city has charisma and is full of history at every street corner. Not to be missed is the spectacular Exeter Cathedral.

properties.name: Bournemouth
properties.shortnarra: A sandy hideaway on the south coast and fast attracting the attentions of clubbers, shoppers and professional surfers keen to take advantage of the laid back atmosphere and opportunities here.

properties.name: Bristol
properties.shortnarra: Important city, once a much more influential port than it is now, with many winding streets, old buildings and a beautiful cathedral to boot.

properties.name: Bath
properties.shortnarra: Some of the finest architectural sights in Europe can be found in this laid-back city; the city is so much more than its famous Roman Baths and the hot-springs which can still be found here.

properties.name: FRANCE
properties.shortnarra: England's closest contact with mainland Europe offers delicious food, passionate people and beautiful places. Cities pound with culture while villages bustle along with traditional Gallic charm.

properties.name: Castries
properties.shortnarra: Capital city of Saint Lucia.

properties.name: Manchester
properties.narrative: Manchester does not have the 'zip' that Leeds does, and nor does it have the greenery of Sheffield, but it perhaps most fittingly wears the moniker of 'Capital of the North'. It has its own secret. When you arrive in Manchester, by car or by rail, you fe
properties.shortnarra: Unofficial 'Capital of the North' with a 'hands in pockets' attitude and a shrugged shoulders nonchalence. All delivered up in a characterstic nasal whiiiiiiiine (see 'Oasis' for details).

properties.name: Cardiff
properties.shortnarra: The capital of Wales and home to a huge castle and The Millennium Stadium - the mecca of all things rugby.

properties.name: Swansea
properties.shortnarra: Beautiful second-city of Wales, with long, golden, sandy beaches fringed with trees, a very long history and a currently vibrant nightlife.

properties.name: Canterbury
properties.shortnarra: Ancient and beautiful walled and cobbled city, bustling around the oldest cathedral in England. The playwright Christopher Marlowe was born here - the place absolutely reeks of history.

properties.name: Brighton
properties.shortnarra: A thumping party-town, admirably liberal in its attitudes and affectionately known as 'London-On-Sea'.

properties.name: Portsmouth
properties.shortnarra: Sparkling waterfront city whose fortunes are ever linked to the sea and sailing. You can visit ancient crumbling ruins during the day, do a spot of shopping, then dance till you drop later on ...

properties.name: Southampton
properties.shortnarra: Apparently the 'Cruise Capital of Northern Europe', Southampton is another city which is proud of its maritime heritage.

properties.name: Chi?in?u
properties.shortnarra: Capital City of Moldova.

properties.name: ESTONIA
properties.shortnarra: Bears, lynxes, wolves lurk in the deep forests of the country. The stunning capital, Tallin, has possibly the best preserved medieval centre in Europe. Add perfect uncrowded beaches, and you're there.

properties.name: Helsinki
properties.shortnarra: Capital City of Finland (since 1812)

properties.name: Minsk
properties.shortnarra: Capital City of Belarus.

properties.name: Central Federal District of EUROPEAN RUSSIA
Pitcairns Islands
properties.narrative: <span class="Apple-style-span">The islands are the last British colony in the South Pacific and most isolated British dependency. The rugged main island was settled by the infamous mutineers of the HMS Bounty and their Polynesian companions, and most of
properties.shortnarra: Loosely grouped handful of tiny islands in the remote South Pacific, farther from any continent than any other inhabited island.

properties.name: Bucharest
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of Romania

properties.name: Canary Islands
Madrid
properties.shortnarra: The pulsating heart and capital city of Spain.

properties.name: Esztergom
properties.shortnarra: Historic capital of the ancient Magyar kingdom

properties.name: MOLDOVA
properties.narrative: Ungheni is a particularly beautiful city and ought not be missed.
properties.shortnarra: A once secretive country, now opening up its doors to tourism, this country has an absolute glut of vinyards, wine cellars (some of which extend for 150 miles) and ... monasteries.

properties.name: SLOVENIA
properties.shortnarra: A mountainous and forested, often overlooked European gem. Slovenia's slightly difficult to pronounce capital Ljubljana is thriving and becoming popular with adventurous city-break types.

properties.name: MONTENEGRO
properties.narrative: Couple this with friendly and enthusiastic people, an outdoors mentality (Montenegro has some SERIOUSLY impressive canyons) and you've got a European secret which hasn't yet been discovered.
properties.shortnarra: A simply beautiful place, Montenegro is Europe in miniature. Dark mountains and forests (bears and wolves included), azure-blue sea lapping at white and sandy coasts and ancient towns and villages.

properties.name: Podgorica
properties.shortnarra: Capital city of Montenegro

properties.name: Kiruna
properties.shortnarra: The largest city in the world (by area). And being moved for the iron industry.

properties.name: Riga
properties.shortnarra: Capital city of Latvia.

properties.name: CZECH REPUBLIC
properties.shortnarra: If you're adventurous, there's more here than good-value city-breaks to its capital, Prague. In the south of the country, medieval towns are sprinkled everywhere - go off-track and find your own CR.

properties.name: MALLORCA
properties.shortnarra: Often overpopulated by Europeans seeking some sunshine and sea, Mallorca (or Majorca) has always been a popular playground. There is plenty to explore on this island paradise.

properties.name: Kiev
properties.shortnarra: Capital City of the Ukraine.

properties.name: Winchester
properties.shortnarra: Former ancient capital of England

properties.name: Chichester
properties.shortnarra: A beautiful, ancient cathedral city with tonnes to keep you sightseeing for a couple of days.

properties.name: Vienna
properties.shortnarra: Capital city of Austria.

properties.name: Reykjavik
properties.shortnarra: Vibrant capital city of Iceland

properties.name: Bern
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of Switzerland and one time home of Mr Albert Einstein.

properties.name: Rome
properties.shortnarra: The always fascinating, always beautiful, capital of Italy.

properties.name: Newcastle Upon Tyne
properties.narrative: Historically a part of Northumberland, this tough little town has spread from the 'new' castle and the river. The city developed in the area that was the location of the Roman settlement called Pons Aelius, though it owes its
properties.shortnarra: Strange beer, strange language but mix with the very friendly locals and you simply won't care ...

properties.name: RUSSIA
properties.shortnarra: The largest country in the world, and one of the coldest ...

properties.name: Cape Town
properties.shortnarra: The legislative capital city of South Africa.

properties.name: H�fn ('Hup')
properties.shortnarra: Beautiful coastal town - famous for being pronounced more like an unexpected hiccup ("hup")

properties.name: Amsterdam
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of Amsterdam.

properties.name: The Hague
properties.shortnarra: Or, as the Dutch call it, 'Den Haag'

properties.name: Oslo
properties.shortnarra: Capital of a race of people only 15 or so generations removed from their warrior, trader and traveler Viking incarnation. Oslo is stunning, clean and culturally rich - turn the tables and visit THEM.

properties.name: Berlin
properties.shortnarra: Throbbing, unpredictable and party-loving capital of Germany.

properties.name: BELARUS
properties.shortnarra: An unspoilt country, proud of its pagan roots and folk traditions. There's always the odd folk festival going on. Berezinsky nature reserve is a primeval forest which conceals wolves, beaver and boar.

properties.name: Vilnius
properties.shortnarra: Capital city of Lithuania.

properties.name: Nottingham
properties.narrative:
A modern, bustling, rambling city and informally known as 'The Queen of the Midlands'. Quite who the King of the Midlands is, is moot.

Nottingham is of course famous for Robin Hood. And lace, the pharmacist 'Boots' and many other things including
properties.shortnarra: A city dominated now, as it was historically, by the powerful castle. Much heralded in Robin Hood stories the city's streets are much haunted by this mythical character's name.

properties.name: Lancaster
properties.narrative: A lot of the town winds around the imposing Norman castle, wedged firmly on Castle Hill. The streets are crammed full of bustling shops, bars and restaurants. All of this a very short drive from the wide open and wild landscapes of the Lake District. Thi
properties.shortnarra: Ancient city with a history going back over eight hundred years.

properties.name: Leeds
properties.narrative:
Leeds is a commercial, legal and financial powerhouse. There is no avoiding it and it casts a mighty shadow over its neighbours in all three areas.

The city centre feels quite imposing and a little claustrophobic. There is not an awful lot of gre
properties.shortnarra: A thundering upstart, outpacing nearby Manchester and Sheffield both commercially and financially. This gothic city has cultural gems to visit, and in the evening, makes for a sophisticated night out.

properties.name: York
properties.narrative: This is a beautiful, 2,000 year old city - fought fiercely for by Roman, Viking and Norman. It contains the largest medieval church in Europe within crumbling city walls, higgledy-piggledy narrow winding lanes, shady spots and unpronounceable street name
properties.shortnarra: This city, which gave the county of Yorkshire its name, appears to have ignored the Industrial Revolution and as consequence, feels one of the most authentically medieval cities in the country.

properties.name: Liverpool
properties.narrative: Liverpool has always relied on the sea for its trade and the cargo delivered from it - whether that was people, fish or other goods. As such, the docks are huge. In fact, at last count, there are seven miles of dock stretched along the waterfront. Liverp
properties.shortnarra: The city which nurtured the Beatles is now busily reinventing itself. It has two cathedrals, one of which is the second largest in the world (after St Peter's, in Rome)

properties.name: Sofia
properties.shortnarra: Capital City of Bulgaria.

properties.name: Sarajevo
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of Bosnia and Herzegonia.

properties.name: Aurillac
properties.shortnarra: The Cantal region looks to Aurillac as its tourist centre.

properties.name: Birmingham
properties.narrative: <!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument> <w:View>Normal</w:View> <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom> <w:Compatibility> <w:BreakWrappedTables/> <w:SnapToGridInCell/> <w:WrapTextWithPunct/> <w:UseAsianBreakRules/> </w:Compatibility> <w:BrowserLevel>MicrosoftInternetExplor
properties.shortnarra: This is Britain?s second largest city.

properties.name: Hereford
properties.narrative:

 <w:WordDocument>

properties.shortnarra: The city in which Nell Gwynne was born is also known for its cider production. It is bordered in the south by the River Wye and there?s an attractive medieval bridge here.

properties.name: Kamyanets-Podilsky (?????????-???????????)
properties.shortnarra: The beautiful medieval city on a "rock" in the river. One of the most beautiful sites in Ukraine.

properties.name: Clermont-Ferrand
properties.narrative:
The 17th century philosopher Blaise Pascal was born here and the city is the centre of the Michelin Tyre industry.

This area is riddled with extinct volcanoes and the original settlement of Clermont was actually established on an extinct volcano.
properties.shortnarra: Capital of the department of Puy-de-Dome and the centre (both geographically and economically) of the Massif Central region.

properties.name: Gloucester
properties.narrative: The Roman routes through the city are still there; the names of these and the various routes into and out of the city are still there (Eastgate, Northgate for example). There are ancient buildings here ? once inns ? which surround inner courtyards, again
properties.shortnarra: This city was important Roman Fort, for it guarded the busiest Severn crossing at this part of the river. It was the Romans route into Wales and where the Domesday Survey was planned.

properties.name: Brussels
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of Belgium.

properties.name: Tallinn
properties.shortnarra: Captivating and beautiful capital city of Estonia, comprising possibly the best medieval centre in Europe.

properties.name: Ripon
properties.narrative:
Every night, at 9pm, you can see (and of course hear) the man known as 'The Ripon Hornblower' blowing a horn on each corner of the obelisk in the market square.

This custom of setting the watch originates with the wakemen of Ripon who were mediev
properties.shortnarra: A 1,300 year old market town with city status, Ripon has plenty to see and do, and is rooted in its history.

properties.name: Luxembourg City
properties.shortnarra: The highly original capital city of ... Luxembourg!

properties.name: Vaduz
properties.shortnarra: The capital of Liechtenstein.

properties.name: Golfito
properties.narrative:

properties.shortnarra: Quiet town in the south. Was built by the Int. fruit Company in the 50's. Famous for Sportfishing, the duty free zone and no place to stay for long - according to Lonely Planet :/

properties.name: Sneek
properties.shortnarra: Ancient city, full of canals, and which dates back to the 10th century. Don't miss the rather unique Waterport. And please don't fail to appreciate the fantastic name of this city.

properties.name: Bratislava
properties.shortnarra: Capital City of Slovakia.

properties.name: Wells
properties.shortnarra: This compact medieval city - the smallest city in England - is a well-kept secret. Wells gets its name from the springs which still bubble up here. It makes a superb base to explore Somerset.

properties.name: Sunderland
properties.narrative:
However, it is a city with a modern, bustling centre and a relaxing green environment. There is breathtaking coastal scenery only a short drive away.

Its fortunes really rested on shipbuilding, like Newcastle, but it's been m
properties.shortnarra: Sunderland, perhaps unfairly, has a rather bad image; a slightly down-at-heel place cowering in the shadow of its glitzy, fashionable neighbour Newcastle.

properties.name: Washington DC
properties.shortnarra: Capital of the United States of America.

properties.name: Skopje
properties.shortnarra: Capital city of Macedonia.

properties.name: Edinburgh
properties.shortnarra: The absolutely jaw-droppingly beautiful capital city of Scotland and the most highly populated area in this beautiful country.

properties.name: HUNGARY
properties.shortnarra: Proud and ancient nation, recently emerged from a cloak of communism. Hungary offers innovation and history in equal measure. The capital is the same - Buda offers history, Pest lots of places to play.

properties.name: SAN MARINO
properties.narrative: The rest of this state is pretty streets and tourism, tourism, tourism. There are plenty of places to eat and plenty of places to 'hang out'.
properties.shortnarra: The third smallest independent state in the world has its historic centre perched on top of a very, very, very high bit of rock.

properties.name: LIECHTENSTEIN
properties.shortnarra: Sixth smallest country in the world, nestling in the middle of Europe. This place is beautiful - hike in the mountains, swim in its mountain lakes or go and party in the city with the friendly locals.

properties.name: POLAND
properties.shortnarra: Being at the crossroads of Europe comes at a price. Poland has seen a fair share of conflict. And survived. Explore its history, vibrant cities and beautiful countryside of mountains, lakes and forest.

properties.name: SERBIA
properties.shortnarra: You may not think it but Serbia has some of the best ski (Kopaonik) and spa resorts in Europe. There're many ancient towns and villages to explore and the capital Belgrade is reinventing itself rapidly

properties.name: Dundee
properties.shortnarra: As in 'Dundee Cake' - NOT as in Crocodile.

properties.name: Perth
properties.shortnarra: Yes, like the one in Australia. But this was here first.

properties.name: Glasgow
properties.shortnarra: Former City of Culture, Glasgow is a thriving, bustling city with something to offer everyone.

properties.name: MONACO
properties.shortnarra: People come to this tiny independent state only to play and to pose. Think numerous casinos, high-end restaurants and bars. And of course, the Grand Prix. Whatever you do, dress well and look good.

properties.name: Prague
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of the Czech Republic.

properties.name: Tirana
properties.shortnarra: Capital city of Albania.

properties.name: PORTUGAL
properties.shortnarra: Portugal may be relatively small, but it punches above its weight; with white, long, sandy beaches and whitewashed old towns, this is the place to kick back and ... relaaaaaaaax.

properties.name: ALBANIA
properties.narrative: At least for the moment - but you'd better move sharply if you want to experience the solitude of this place. People are finding out about its treasures. And quickly.
properties.shortnarra: Wild and lonely beauty pervades this ruin-peppered country. Earnestly stumbling away from communism - Tirana is buzzy as any European city but the countryside - and adventures out there, is your own ..

properties.name: ANDORRA
properties.shortnarra: Smallest state in Europe and perched in the craggy Pyrenees. This set-up lends itself well to both summer (hiking, trekking, camping and fishing) and winter (skiing, tobogganing) outdoor pursuits.

properties.name: MACEDONIA
properties.shortnarra: Mountainous land & former kingdom of Alexander the Great. The west is crammed full of sites, the middle is wine country and has the capital. The east, is rural and you'll see rural Macedonian life.

properties.name: Toledo
properties.narrative: With rickety, narrow and winding lanes, weaving through clusters of ancient buildings, take a step back in time and visit this place. The city itself huddles together in a bend, hugged close by the beautiful Tagus river.
properties.shortnarra: Spain's medieval capital

properties.name: UKRAINE
properties.shortnarra: The Crimean Mountains lie in the Crimean peninsula and the Carpathian Mountains in the west offer skiing, fishing, hunting and many other outdoor pursuits. Don't miss the medieval towns including Odesa

properties.name: Athens
properties.shortnarra: The capital of Greece.

properties.name: Dublin
properties.shortnarra: Capital city of Ireland.

properties.name: Lisbon
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of Portugal.

properties.name: St. Davids
properties.shortnarra: This city is the final resting place of the patron saint of Wales.

properties.name: Praia
properties.shortnarra: The capital city of the Cape Verde Islands.

properties.name: Pretoria
properties.shortnarra: The executive capital city of South Africa.

properties.name: Bloemfontein
properties.shortnarra: The judicial capital city of South Africa.

properties.name: New Delhi
properties.shortnarra: Sprawling, crowded, hot and dusty capital city of India.

properties.name: Kathmandu
properties.shortnarra: Capital City of Nepal.

properties.name: Rye
properties.address: NY State, United States of America
properties.shortnarra: Take down the pace in beautiful Rye, a delicate and urbane town, with plenty of attractions to keep you happy.

properties.name: Las Vegas
properties.shortnarra: The most populous city in Nevada and - let's face it - the only reason you'd really come here is on a stag, a hen, or to engage in a spot of gambling and debauchery. And why not?

properties.name: San Francisco
properties.shortnarra: Trams, hills, alcatraz, The Golden Gate Bridge, friendly locals and fog await you in this beautiful city. Wowee, yes, lots of fog (and a foghorn though).

properties.name: New York
properties.shortnarra: The City. The Capital of the World. The Big Apple. The Empire City. The City So Nice They Named it Twice. This place must be good - it's got so many names.

properties.name: Philadelphia
properties.shortnarra: Come to Philly, city founded by William Penn )and of course features in the Rocky film).
